Cape Town - Cape Town police are investigating a case of murder after the decomposed body of a woman was found along Old Nooiensfontein Road, Kuils River, on Thursday afternoon. It's believed the body had been badly mutilated. Police spokesperson Noloyiso Rwexana said Mfuleni police were investigating. "Be advised thatÂ  Mfuleni police have opened a case of murder for investigation after a body of an unidentified female was found this afternoon at 13:45 in Nooiensfontein road. "Circumstances surrounding this incident are being investigated with no one arrested at this stage of the investigation," she said. Anyone with information is requested to come forward.  argusnews@inl.co.za  Cape Argus